codex
The patch mostly implements the timestamp representation change, but it introduces an error-taxonomy regression on malformed consolidation verdicts. That is a caller-visible contract break that should be fixed before considering the patch correct.

Review comment:

- [P2] Map malformed consolidation timestamps to Consolidator — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15b/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:4996-4999
  When a consolidation provider returns an `invalidate` verdict with a malformed or non-string `t_invalid`, `normalize_extractor_timestamp` now propagates `EngineError::InvalidArgument` from this `?`. That violates the documented `Consolidator` leaf for malformed provider verdicts, so callers/bindings will misclassify a provider protocol fault as a bad user argument in exactly the bad-timestamp scenario TC-33 is hardening.
